Full Description: Money laundering needs to be a collective effort through centralised intelligence-gathering. For this reason  Tookitaki developed the AML Ecosystem  which includes our network of experts and the Typology Repository (TR).  The AML ecosystem is a game changer since it helps remove the information vacuum created by siloed AML operations. It also lays the foundation of a  democratized detection approach where AML behavioural models are shared across an ecosystem through a privacy-protected framework. Our network of experts includes risk advisers  legal firms  AML specialists  consultancies  and financial institutions from across the globe. Driven by effective collaboration between experts  the TR has grown exponentially over the past few months.In addition to our AML ecosystem  which is a first-of-its-kind community-driven initiative  we have Tookitaki’s Anti-Money Laundering Suite or AMLS for our customers. The AMLS is an operating system comprising of four modules  such as Transaction Monitoring  Smart Screening  Customer Risk Scoring and the Case Manager  under one roof to address our customers’ compliance requirements. It provides holistic risk coverage  sharper detection  and significantly fewer false alerts.  It can be deployed in multiple environments including the public cloud  private cloud  and data centre.Tookitaki’s AML Ecosystem and the AMLS work in tandem and help our stakeholders widen their view of risk from an internal one to an industry-wide one across organizations and borders. Moreover  they can do so without compromising privacy and security. Founded in November 2014  Tookitaki employs over 100 people across Asia  Europe  the Middle East  and the Americas. Tookitaki’s innovations in regulatory compliance have been acknowledged worldwide. Chartis Research named the company a Rising Star in its 2021 RiskTech 100 report. In 2020   the company won the Regulation Asia  Awards for Excellence and the G20TechSprint  accelerator. In  2019  the company was featured in the World Economic Forum’s Technology Pioneer List.
Industries: Compliance  Finance  FinTech  Predictive Analytics  SaaS  Software

Full Description: Fabrica AI is creating a future where ideating and developing a robot for any task takes days  not years. We believe that by training end to end controls in simulation with reinforcement learning and above that iterating hardware designs  we can automate the whole development process. At the current stage  the most important resource is a large fleet of robots to validate our approaches for our AI system and to collect data. This would help keep us grounded in reality. To start building up the fleet  we invented an automatic tile grouting robot that boosts productivity by 5x and are piloting it on construction sites in Singapore managed by Woh Hup  BHCC  Gin Chia  Soilbuild  and Dragages. We have early leads in the US and Europe as well. Tile grouting is the process of filling up the gaps between tiles after the tiles have been laid. Grouting is part of virtually every construction project and a highly laborious process  is considered one of the most physically damaging tasks resulting in tilers’ knees and back issues  and thus quality issues would also arise.  We invented a patent pending robot that is able to automatically grout and clean tile gaps with only a press of a button. The operators would only need to reload grout and water.We are headquartered in Delaware  and have offices in Singapore and Brno  Czech Republic. Demo locations include Zurich  Miami  London/Cambridge  and Vienna.

Features of Pangu Architecture:1. The cost of the computing power engaged in the jobs depends the amount of payment. More than 2 miners will be assigned to one task so as to increase the return rate; their results will be verified with each other in order to ensure the accuracy of the results simply.3. Blockchain make the status of these tasks become open and transparent. Information includes the miners responsible for computing  the computing duration and so on. By doing so  some existing problems in the DC products such as black-box operation will be addressed.4. Task assignment mechanism is designed to make cloud computing safer by eliminating the possibility that miners cannot assemble the whole picture of one job in spite that they are computing many tasks in one job.5. Mist computing will reduce the dependence in the cloud computing.6. Whitelist mechanism only allows users with ID verfication to use the system so as to aviod malicious use.7. Full Description: Fall is a big issue. Globally  there are 600 000 deaths & 37 million injuries every year. Full Description: Einsights was set up to solve a burning problem that is being exacerbated by the explosion in data generation – “How can they leverage data to make informed decisions that will unlock profits within my organisation or for my client?” The only logical answer was to deploy sophisticated technology in a manner that is transparent to the end user.Their humble beginnings can be traced back to eight rooms globally as the company started off with a virtual team (a great story over a drink someday!) and their first office was in a warehouse in Singapore (since it’s hard to find garages). Like most companies starting out  they had long delivery nights with pizzas and Cola  but they also had fun. Like most companies  they also struggled initially but were determined. Our metamorphosis into a company with operations in seven countries has been predominantly through word-of-mouth by clients and employees who are enthralled by their work.As the complexity in their daily life increases  they yearn for simplicity. The products that have changed lives have a common underlying theme – simplicity; for simplicity reduces stress and increases happiness in their lives.At Einsights  simplicity is deeply engrained in their DNA and is reflected in everything from product design to the user experience. Our mission is to democratise data and to simplify the corporate decision making process.They are creating a product that is beautiful yet powerful. They do use sophisticated technologies such as Artificial Intelligence and Natural Language Processing but they are transparent to the end user for the best feature they offer is the intuitive design.They are not just about insights and analysis – although they do that really well. At their core lies a passion to simplify lives.

Full Description: Raritan Computer  Inc. manufactures KVM  serial  power  monitoring  and management solutions. It provides solutions that monitor  access  control  and manage servers and other IT devices in data centers  server rooms  and remote offices. The company's products include KVM-over-IP switches that provide BIOS-level access and control of servers over LAN  WAN  Internet connection  or dialup; analog KVM switches  which offer the power to access and control servers and other network devices in data center or server room; and power management solutions that allow IT administrators and facilities managers to monitor  access  and control power at the rack. It also provides serial console solutions  which offer control of serial devices  such as routers  switches  firewalls  and servers; network monitoring hardware and virtual monitoring appliances; and centralized management solutions  which offer a granular system for controlling and auditing various user and administrator transactions. In addition  the company provides embedded server management products that offer architecture for server OEM  motherboard manufacturer  system builder  or other embedded computing solutions; and a range of device accessories and rack management solutions. It provides solutions for data centers  server rooms  power management  remote office management  government  disaster recovery/hosted/colocation  desktop/small office  and computer server manufacturers. Raritan Computer  Inc. has a strategic technology partnership with Innovative Research. The company was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Somerset  New Jersey with operations in Zwickau  Germany.
